HEADWORD: Imprese
<hw>Im*prese"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A device. See
<er>Impresa</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An <qex>imprese</qex>, as the Italians call it, is a device in
picture with his motto or word, borne by noble or learned
personages.</q> <rj><qau>Camden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impress</ent>⟦br⟧
